    {
      "id": "note_summary",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## How the NEW flow works\n\n1. **12 named stages** orchestrated by `pipeline.py`. Each stage runs inside `stage_runner(stage=..., tracer=..., logger=..., metrics=...)` — uniform span / event / metric emission.\n2. **Inspectors plug into stage 3 (classify)**. JailbreakDetector also runs here (via the jailbreak/ subpackage).\n3. **Strategies plug into stage 7 (execute)** via the `registry` (5 built-in + extensible).\n4. **Research subpackages own their own stages**: intent/ → defend, deception/ → deception_inspect, fidelity/ → verify, rehydration/ → rehydrate.\n5. **Branching at stage 7**: `blocked` → refusal envelope; `pass` → verify + rehydrate. Both rejoin at decision_emit + report.\n6. **Adapters (NATS, Unleash, Webhook)** are NOT in pip/ anymore — moved to backlog §4.2 to keep the SDK provider-neutral. Operators implement Reporter Protocol externally.\n\n**Class count**: 3 inspectors + 5 strategies + 2 reporters + 2 flag providers (in pip/) + 12 new subpackages owning their own Protocol surfaces.",
      "x": 1737,
      "y": 847,
      "width": 603,
      "height": 593,
      "color": "3"
    },
